WEBVTT

00:01.083 --> 00:05.083
♪♪

00:05.709 --> 00:10.959
♪♪

00:10.959 --> 00:11.875
(groans)

00:11.875 --> 00:13.917
-What's up?
-What?

00:13.917 --> 00:17.375
What's---what--
what is that music?

00:17.375 --> 00:20.041
Are we listening to
the funeral home station?

00:20.041 --> 00:22.709
No, we're listening
to my prototype.

00:22.709 --> 00:24.959
JEN: What?

00:24.959 --> 00:28.250
Yeah, it's turning
Lark's cries

00:28.250 --> 00:30.792
into soothing music.

00:30.792 --> 00:34.083
May I present: CryTunes.

00:34.083 --> 00:38.125
Yeah, I posted
it at my work.

00:38.125 --> 00:40.834
We're live, baby,
and raising funds.

00:40.834 --> 00:43.792
Oh, so you are crowdfunding
your own idea.

00:43.792 --> 00:45.709
Yeah, see, got
a little description,

00:45.709 --> 00:48.458
and these are all the rewards
that backers can get.

00:48.458 --> 00:51.959
JEN: "$100,
personalized mixtape."

00:51.959 --> 00:53.917
Well, yeah, I mean,
I'm the king of those.

00:53.917 --> 00:56.917
So what do you think?

00:56.917 --> 00:58.291
Who? Oh, me?

00:58.291 --> 00:59.542
Um...

00:59.542 --> 01:01.250
-You don't like it.
-I--

01:01.250 --> 01:03.333
You know what,
it feels a little bit

01:03.333 --> 01:06.625
like I'm, like,
shopping for curtains

01:06.625 --> 01:09.166
at a high-end outdoor mall.

01:09.166 --> 01:11.375
Well, uh, you can
change the music.

01:11.375 --> 01:12.875
(electronic dance music plays)

01:12.875 --> 01:15.792
-Huh?
-No, no, no, no.

01:15.792 --> 01:18.125
Well, no, I mean, you can--
it can be any kind of music.

01:18.125 --> 01:20.041
-It doesn't have to be--
-Yeah, not this one.

01:20.041 --> 01:21.417
It doesn't have
to be these two,

01:21.417 --> 01:22.834
but the music
will keep going

01:22.834 --> 01:25.000
as long as Lark
keeps crying.

01:25.000 --> 01:27.834
Greg, Lark is crying.

01:27.834 --> 01:29.709
-No, no, no, Lark is crying.
-Oh.

01:29.709 --> 01:32.709
JEN: Yeah, she's a living baby.
GREG: Sorry!

01:32.709 --> 01:33.625
(chimes)

01:33.625 --> 01:35.291
Yes, 25%!

01:35.291 --> 01:38.166
Take that,
documentaries about anime.

01:38.166 --> 01:40.959
(knocking)

01:40.959 --> 01:42.667
Hey, babe,
what are you doing here?

01:42.667 --> 01:45.500
Um, I came for my mixtape.

01:45.500 --> 01:47.834
-You donated?
-Yeah, yeah.

01:47.834 --> 01:51.083
You know, I was, I was feeling
bad about this morning.

01:51.083 --> 01:54.125
I feel like I gave your idea
lukewarm support,

01:54.125 --> 01:55.750
and it should have
been hot, you know?

01:55.750 --> 01:59.125
It should have been
a steaming pile of hot support.

01:59.125 --> 02:00.583
So you believe in it?

02:00.583 --> 02:01.709
Honestly, more than anything,

02:01.709 --> 02:05.542
I was thinking about
how much I believe in you.

02:05.542 --> 02:08.125
Thank you, honey.

02:08.125 --> 02:10.458
Now, if you believe in me
just a hundred bucks more,

02:10.458 --> 02:11.792
your reward is a caricature.

02:11.792 --> 02:13.542
Now, I can give you
big eyes or big boobs.

02:13.542 --> 02:15.166
Which do you want?
I draw 'em both the same.

02:15.166 --> 02:16.083
(chimes)

02:16.083 --> 02:17.667
GREG:
30%!

02:17.667 --> 02:19.709
♪♪

02:19.709 --> 02:20.667
(chimes)

02:20.667 --> 02:21.667
Hey, there, Greg.

02:21.667 --> 02:23.417
Saw you posted something
on our website.

02:23.417 --> 02:24.667
Yeah, yeah.

02:24.667 --> 02:26.792
I mean, you can still get in
on the ground floor,

02:26.792 --> 02:28.750
you know, get rich.

02:28.750 --> 02:30.041
I'm already rich.

02:30.041 --> 02:31.458
See, here's the thing.

02:31.458 --> 02:33.333
Posting your own product is, uh,

02:33.333 --> 02:34.834
it's a conflict of interest.

02:34.834 --> 02:36.625
You know, it's like, uh--

02:36.625 --> 02:38.417
oh, it's like taking
your sister-in-law

02:38.417 --> 02:40.750
to a drive-in movie
and getting her drunk

02:40.750 --> 02:44.542
on a little apple wine
and making out with her,

02:44.542 --> 02:47.041
and then regretting it later.

02:47.041 --> 02:48.375
It's just not done.

02:48.375 --> 02:51.417
But, uh, we, we--
we're-we're 50% funded

02:51.417 --> 02:52.917
in just under three hours.

02:52.917 --> 02:54.792
I mean, even the ball wipe guys,

02:54.792 --> 02:56.667
it took them
a month to do that.

02:56.667 --> 02:59.041
The creators of Cleanuts
don't work here.

02:59.041 --> 03:01.542
They smoke weed and throw
food at each other's balls.

03:01.542 --> 03:03.250
That's how they came
up with the idea.

03:03.250 --> 03:05.291
Are you saying the entire
time that I work here,

03:05.291 --> 03:06.917
I can't do anything
creative ever?

03:06.917 --> 03:08.834
I'm not saying that.

03:08.834 --> 03:10.458
I want people to be creative.

03:10.458 --> 03:13.709
If you want to, you know, mix
flavors at the soda fountain

03:13.709 --> 03:16.500
or bring in a jigsaw puzzle,

03:16.500 --> 03:18.458
I think it'd be great.

03:18.458 --> 03:21.500
The point is I would take
it down, if I were you,

03:21.500 --> 03:24.125
but that's just me.

03:24.125 --> 03:26.333
You dig?

03:26.333 --> 03:28.792
♪♪

03:28.792 --> 03:31.625
Anyway, I'm just glad Greg's
feeling inspired, you know?

03:31.625 --> 03:35.041
I mean, aside from Lark
and our smoke alarm going off

03:35.041 --> 03:36.792
every time we cook a steak,

03:36.792 --> 03:39.083
there's really not much
excitement in our house.

03:39.083 --> 03:43.291
Well, that's about to change.

03:44.917 --> 03:46.041
Uh, what's up?

03:46.041 --> 03:53.083
♪♪

03:55.291 --> 03:56.458
Hi.

03:56.458 --> 03:58.125
Uh, you're,
you're home early.

03:58.125 --> 04:02.000
Yeah, well, um,
I got some big news.

04:02.000 --> 04:03.375
-So do I, um--
-Yeah, well,

04:03.375 --> 04:05.041
let me go first,
'cause I'm taller.

04:05.041 --> 04:09.041
So CryTunes has reached
twice its funding goal

04:09.041 --> 04:10.083
in its first day.

04:10.083 --> 04:11.792
Wow, that--that's amazing.

04:11.792 --> 04:15.041
And how would you feel about
me maybe quitting my job

04:15.041 --> 04:17.458
to focus solely on,
on CryTunes?

04:17.458 --> 04:18.458
And before you answer,

04:18.458 --> 04:21.667
know that I may have
already quit my job.

04:21.667 --> 04:25.875
You, you, you "may have"
quit your job?

04:25.875 --> 04:27.792
I quit my job.

04:27.792 --> 04:30.625
There were ultimatums given,
uh, of a legal nature.

04:30.625 --> 04:32.041
I don't want
to bore you with--

04:32.041 --> 04:34.375
-I'm a lawyer, Greg.
GREG: But after you came in,

04:34.375 --> 04:36.083
it just really pumped
me up, you know?

04:36.083 --> 04:38.750
And, and I can't
do this without you,

04:38.750 --> 04:40.792
so I know it's gonna
be hard around here.

04:40.792 --> 04:42.959
You know, we're gonna have
to tighten some belts--

04:42.959 --> 04:45.667
Actually, I think I'm
gonna have to loosen mine.

04:47.875 --> 04:49.250
I'm pregnant.

04:51.959 --> 04:54.458
(smooth jazz plays)

04:58.208 --> 05:01.583
♪♪

05:01.583 --> 05:03.291
John was there
from the beginning,

05:03.291 --> 05:05.792
when Karyl and I first
worked the same flight.

05:05.792 --> 05:07.125
JOHN:
Yeah, I remember that.

05:07.125 --> 05:08.417
Carol was my copilot,

05:08.417 --> 05:11.333
and Karyl with a "K"
was a stewardess.

05:11.333 --> 05:13.375
I remember I asked 'em
to bring some nuts

05:13.375 --> 05:15.458
up to the cockpit,
but they were in the lav.

05:15.458 --> 05:19.083
And, you know, nuts were
the last thing on their mind.

05:19.083 --> 05:20.750
HEATHER: Hey, Aunt Carol!

05:20.750 --> 05:22.500
CAROL: Oh, sweetheart.
HEATHER: Hi.

05:22.500 --> 05:24.250
KARYL: Hi.

05:24.250 --> 05:26.458
HEATHER: Congratulations
on your wedding.

05:26.458 --> 05:28.208
JOAN: Isn't it
wonderful, honey?

05:28.208 --> 05:29.959
Over 35 years,

05:29.959 --> 05:31.834
and now they can
make it legal.

05:31.834 --> 05:33.542
And now you can, too, huh?

05:33.542 --> 05:34.875
What's that?

05:34.875 --> 05:35.834
Nothing.

05:35.834 --> 05:37.083
CAROL: Oh.

05:37.083 --> 05:38.458
What, what is it, Mom?

05:38.458 --> 05:41.333
Oh, it, it's wine, honey.

05:41.333 --> 05:42.583
Okay, what's happening?

05:42.583 --> 05:44.750
Why will no one make
eye contact with me?

05:44.750 --> 05:46.208
Aunt Carols?

05:48.959 --> 05:51.041
Fasten your seatbelt, hon.

05:51.041 --> 05:53.291
Okay, you guys, come on,
I'm a grown-up.

05:53.291 --> 05:55.542
Whatever it is,
I can handle this.

05:55.542 --> 05:57.667
Your mother and I
aren't married.

05:59.125 --> 06:00.500
Mommy?

06:00.500 --> 06:03.000
Honey, it was 1980.

06:03.000 --> 06:05.458
Carol and Karyl
couldn't get married,

06:05.458 --> 06:08.458
so your dad and I
divorced in protest.

06:08.458 --> 06:13.291
So you've been divorced
for 35 years?

06:13.291 --> 06:15.000
Uh, yeah.

06:15.000 --> 06:17.417
JOHN: We've always been
very married in our hearts,

06:17.417 --> 06:19.041
which is all that matters.

06:19.041 --> 06:20.291
This explains so much.

06:20.291 --> 06:22.542
This is--
I'm a child of divorce.

06:22.542 --> 06:24.709
This is why I lick doorknobs,
this is why--

06:24.709 --> 06:26.417
Wait, do Matt and
Greg know about this?

06:26.417 --> 06:28.667
JOAN: We thought it best
not to tell all of you,

06:28.667 --> 06:30.208
so, please, don't
bother your brothers--

06:30.208 --> 06:33.083
HEATHER: Matt, Matt!
JOAN: Oh, Heather, please.

06:33.083 --> 06:35.458
She never was
my best listener.

06:35.458 --> 06:36.959
KARYL:
Mmm.

06:36.959 --> 06:40.834
Colleen, we work together...

06:40.834 --> 06:43.792
HEATHER:
Matt, Matt!

06:43.792 --> 06:45.417
Uh, am I interrupting something?

06:45.417 --> 06:47.458
Huh? No. What's up?

06:47.458 --> 06:49.417
I have got some news

06:49.417 --> 06:51.417
that is going
to shake you to--

06:51.417 --> 06:53.208
okay, can you please
turn her around?

06:53.208 --> 06:54.125
Yeah.

06:54.125 --> 06:55.917
(thudding)

06:55.917 --> 06:56.959
HEATHER: Okay.

06:56.959 --> 06:59.917
Mom and Dad got a divorce,

06:59.917 --> 07:02.375
and they never told us.

07:02.375 --> 07:03.375
What?

07:03.375 --> 07:04.667
Yeah.

07:04.667 --> 07:05.834
Is this my fault?

07:05.834 --> 07:08.583
Oh, no, no,
it's not your fault.

07:08.583 --> 07:11.458
Am I going to have to choose
whose garage to move into?

07:11.458 --> 07:13.458
JOHN:
Now, whatever happened to Murph?

07:13.458 --> 07:15.583
CAROL:
Oh, Murph, hell of a pilot.

07:15.583 --> 07:16.959
He died at an airshow.

07:16.959 --> 07:19.291
Oh, damn, damn,
a daredevil, though.

07:19.291 --> 07:21.500
No, he choked on
a funnel cake.

07:21.500 --> 07:23.000
-Oh.
-You know, for all the times

07:23.000 --> 07:24.625
you guys judged me
for getting divorced,

07:24.625 --> 07:26.000
at least I told people,
or, you know,

07:26.000 --> 07:28.208
they saw the cop car in the
front yard and just assumed.

07:28.208 --> 07:30.375
HEATHER: All right,
the only the way to handle this

07:30.375 --> 07:32.208
is you have to get remarried.

07:32.208 --> 07:33.375
Right now.

07:33.375 --> 07:35.792
You know, I think
you're both overreacting.

07:35.792 --> 07:37.041
Overreacting?

07:37.041 --> 07:39.125
We now come
from a broken home.

07:39.125 --> 07:41.417
I'm probably going to end up
becoming a stripper.

07:41.417 --> 07:43.375
JOHN: Well, look,
it didn't affect anything.

07:43.375 --> 07:44.917
Honestly, we just forgot.

07:44.917 --> 07:46.458
Well, we didn't
both forget.

07:46.458 --> 07:49.041
JOHN: Yeah, we didn't want to
disrupt the family over this.

07:49.041 --> 07:50.667
Oh, so, so, so
all this time,

07:50.667 --> 07:52.959
you just--you stayed
divorced for the kids?

07:52.959 --> 07:54.000
Yeah!

07:54.000 --> 07:56.500
You're such
a wonderful family.

07:56.500 --> 07:58.750
JOAN:
<i>Karyl is just glowing.</i>

07:58.750 --> 08:00.834
I'm happy for you both.

08:00.834 --> 08:01.792
Cheers.

08:01.792 --> 08:03.458
Are you a little jealous?

08:03.458 --> 08:05.500
-No!
-A little bit?

08:05.500 --> 08:07.417
I mean, I always thought
we'd get remarried,

08:07.417 --> 08:08.625
but it doesn't matter.

08:08.625 --> 08:10.000
CAROL:
It's never too late.

08:10.000 --> 08:11.166
Ask him to marry you.

08:11.166 --> 08:12.583
I'd never do that.

08:12.583 --> 08:14.166
CAROL:
I asked Karyl.

08:14.166 --> 08:16.041
We were flying
back from Guatemala.

08:16.041 --> 08:18.291
Customs asked me if
I had anything to declare.

08:18.291 --> 08:19.875
I said,
"Six cartons of cigarettes

08:19.875 --> 08:21.625
and the love
of this good woman."

08:21.625 --> 08:22.750
(laughing)

08:22.750 --> 08:23.667
Wonderful.

08:23.667 --> 08:25.375
GREG:
Liars!

08:25.375 --> 08:29.667
JOHN:
Well, they just told Greg.

08:29.667 --> 08:31.208
When did they divorce?

08:31.959 --> 08:33.917
1980.

08:33.917 --> 08:35.000
1980?

08:35.000 --> 08:36.375
-Yeah.
-No.

08:36.375 --> 08:38.792
I, I, I was born in 1981.

08:38.792 --> 08:40.000
Uh...

08:42.208 --> 08:44.125
Which means...

08:44.125 --> 08:46.083
I'm a...

08:46.083 --> 08:48.625
-Bastard.
-Oh, oh, oh.

08:50.959 --> 08:53.583
God, it almost
makes it worth it.

08:53.583 --> 08:54.917
You old bastard.

08:54.917 --> 08:58.834
♪♪

08:58.834 --> 09:01.125
You're playing with an app
that changes your hairstyle.

09:01.125 --> 09:03.083
Hey, look at
this handsome guy.

09:05.875 --> 09:08.583
♪♪

09:08.583 --> 09:10.917
Oh, man, I am so glad
I got this thing.

09:10.917 --> 09:12.667
This way I can look
at my patients' files

09:12.667 --> 09:15.667
and I can video conference
with my fellow doctors.

09:15.667 --> 09:18.041
You're playing with an app
that changes your hairstyle.

09:18.041 --> 09:19.542
Well, that may not
seem important

09:19.542 --> 09:21.208
to able-haired people
like yourself,

09:21.208 --> 09:22.291
but to me, it is.

09:22.291 --> 09:24.375
Ugh, I don't know how you
can sit there and do that

09:24.375 --> 09:27.125
knowing that my parents'
marriage is a complete fraud.

09:27.125 --> 09:29.250
It's not a fraud,
it was just a lie

09:29.250 --> 09:31.291
that they told you
for your entire life.

09:31.291 --> 09:33.041
Hey, check out
this handsome fella.

09:33.041 --> 09:34.250
HEATHER:
God, put it away.

09:34.250 --> 09:35.166
(door closing)

09:35.166 --> 09:36.083
SOPHIA: Hi, Mom.

09:36.083 --> 09:37.959
Oh, hey, sweetie!

09:37.959 --> 09:39.208
How was school?

09:39.208 --> 09:42.417
Same stuff, different day.

09:42.417 --> 09:45.083
How was Samantha's Student
of the Month ceremony?

09:45.083 --> 09:46.834
(gasping)

09:46.834 --> 09:48.208
Oh, God, oh, no.

09:48.208 --> 09:50.709
I should've known something
was wrong when I had free time!

09:50.709 --> 09:52.667
No mother with free time
is a good mother!

09:52.667 --> 09:54.208
Come on, maybe we can
still make it.

09:54.208 --> 09:55.792
SOPHIA: You can't,
it was hours ago.

09:55.792 --> 09:57.792
TIM: Maybe there's a chance!
-There's no chance.

09:57.792 --> 09:59.000
Maybe the speeches ran long.

09:59.000 --> 10:01.041
Come on, let's go--ow!

10:01.041 --> 10:03.041
HEATHER:
Oh, honey, honey, you okay?

10:03.041 --> 10:04.166
Here, come on, come on.

10:04.166 --> 10:05.917
We gotta go, hang onto me,
hang onto me.

10:05.917 --> 10:07.917
-Yes, you can, yes.
-I can't, I can't make it.

10:07.917 --> 10:09.291
I had two lunches.

10:09.291 --> 10:10.792
-Go on without me!
-No, honey,

10:10.792 --> 10:12.458
I would've never gone
without you.

10:12.458 --> 10:14.542
I want you to be there
so you can share the blame.

10:14.542 --> 10:16.458
Oh, there she is!

10:16.458 --> 10:18.834
You looked so great
up there, sweetie.

10:18.834 --> 10:21.375
I'm so sorry we couldn't stay,
give you a hug and a ride home,

10:21.375 --> 10:24.166
but your dad, he hurt his ankle,
we had to rush out.

10:24.166 --> 10:25.583
I know you weren't there.

10:25.583 --> 10:26.500
What's that?

10:26.500 --> 10:27.417
I was the only kid

10:27.417 --> 10:29.583
without a proud parent
holding up a cell phone.

10:29.583 --> 10:30.792
It was humiliating.

10:30.792 --> 10:32.125
HEATHER:
Sam, Sam, Sam, wait.

10:32.125 --> 10:33.875
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

10:33.875 --> 10:36.625
Okay, yes, you're right,
we weren't there.

10:36.625 --> 10:38.291
And the real reason

10:38.291 --> 10:41.125
that we weren't there
was because...

10:41.125 --> 10:42.583
we were out
buying you this.

10:42.583 --> 10:45.583
Hey, hey, hey--hip, hooray,
hip, hooray, hooray!

10:45.583 --> 10:47.625
I thought you said
I couldn't have one of my own

10:47.625 --> 10:48.750
until I was 16.

10:48.750 --> 10:51.083
Well, that was before
we were so proud of you.

10:51.083 --> 10:52.458
Thank you, I love it!

10:52.458 --> 10:54.250
HEATHER:
Oh, I love you, honey.

10:54.250 --> 10:55.291
Uh, use the railing.

10:55.291 --> 10:57.208
It's not just there
for decoration, now.

10:57.208 --> 10:59.000
(laughing)

10:59.000 --> 11:00.166
Yeah, so, enjoy!

11:00.166 --> 11:01.875
What are you doing?
That was mine!

11:01.875 --> 11:04.375
What? Oh, come on,
that was an epic parent fail.

11:04.375 --> 11:06.375
You have to do something big
to make up for that.

11:08.375 --> 11:10.166
SOPHIA: I've made a list
of all the things

11:10.166 --> 11:11.291
you've missed of mine.

11:11.291 --> 11:13.458
Mm, hope the birth
isn't on there.

11:13.458 --> 11:15.333
HEATHER: Uh, okay,
"One ballet rehearsal,

11:15.333 --> 11:16.667
two soccer games."

11:16.667 --> 11:18.417
I figure that all of this

11:18.417 --> 11:21.250
is worth an overnight
trip to Disneyland

11:21.250 --> 11:23.709
with a souvenir
and a giant turkey leg.

11:23.709 --> 11:25.291
Oh, those turkey legs.

11:25.291 --> 11:28.000
I'll go get started
on the hotel rez.

11:28.000 --> 11:29.917
Do you see the lessons
that we teach them

11:29.917 --> 11:32.000
when we try to buy
their forgiveness?

11:32.000 --> 11:34.125
You know what, you are right,
you are absolutely right.

11:34.125 --> 11:35.542
We have to take
that tablet back.

11:35.542 --> 11:37.083
What, no, then she'll hate us.

11:37.083 --> 11:38.542
Yeah, that's how we know

11:38.542 --> 11:40.959
that we're being good parents.

11:40.959 --> 11:44.500
Then I don't want
to be a good parent.

11:44.500 --> 11:46.625
So we made two
mistakes today.

11:46.625 --> 11:48.458
We forgot your award,

11:48.458 --> 11:50.417
and then we tried
to buy your forgiveness,

11:50.417 --> 11:51.667
which is worse.

11:51.667 --> 11:53.250
We're sorry.

11:53.250 --> 11:54.417
I understand.

11:54.417 --> 11:56.458
Oh, great, 'cause we're gonna
have to take this back.

11:56.458 --> 11:58.041
What are you,
what are you doing, Mom--

11:58.041 --> 11:59.291
Before you get upset again,

11:59.291 --> 12:02.208
just know that we are going to
celebrate your accomplishments

12:02.208 --> 12:04.250
with something better
than an old tablet,

12:04.250 --> 12:05.417
you know?

12:05.417 --> 12:07.166
Dinner!

12:07.166 --> 12:09.291
Weren't you going
to feed me dinner anyway?

12:09.291 --> 12:10.667
No, out, tonight.

12:10.667 --> 12:13.709
Anywhere you want.

12:13.709 --> 12:15.750
Fine. I want to go
to that vegan place

12:15.750 --> 12:16.959
that gives Dad the trots.

12:16.959 --> 12:18.333
Hm, hm.

12:18.333 --> 12:20.000
And I want to bring
all my friends.

12:20.000 --> 12:21.083
Yeah, yeah, yeah, great.

12:21.083 --> 12:23.417
We will go to the restaurant
that gives your dad the trots

12:23.417 --> 12:26.125
and we will watch you and your
friends text for two hours.

12:26.125 --> 12:27.667
-Really?
-Yeah.

12:27.667 --> 12:29.125
This is going to be awesome.

12:29.125 --> 12:31.875
♪♪

12:31.875 --> 12:33.542
Okay, I took
a preemptive Imodium.

12:33.542 --> 12:34.458
Let's do this.

12:34.458 --> 12:36.291
Okay, come on, Sophia,
we're gonna take Sam

12:36.291 --> 12:37.750
and her friends
out to dinner.

12:37.750 --> 12:40.917
You can't take Sam
and her dumb friends to dinner.

12:40.917 --> 12:43.667
Tonight is the party for
Uncle Matt and Colleen's book.

12:43.667 --> 12:46.333
-Oh, sh--
-Seriously?

12:48.166 --> 12:49.959
Here, we got you this.

12:49.959 --> 12:56.291
♪♪

12:56.291 --> 13:00.458
I'm sorry I'm late, but
my Uber got caught in traffic.

13:00.458 --> 13:02.125
Hello, I'm Huber.

13:04.083 --> 13:06.709
♪♪

13:06.709 --> 13:08.542
(indistinct chatter)

13:08.542 --> 13:09.875
This is such a good book.

13:09.875 --> 13:10.792
Oh, thank you.

13:10.792 --> 13:12.458
You know, I have an idea
for a children's book.

13:12.458 --> 13:13.583
Oh.

13:13.583 --> 13:15.250
I went bald when
I was really young

13:15.250 --> 13:16.417
and I sucked at football

13:16.417 --> 13:17.875
and my only friend
was my beagle.

13:17.875 --> 13:20.792
So what about a story like that?

13:20.792 --> 13:23.083
You mean like Charlie Brown?

13:23.083 --> 13:25.458
♪♪

13:25.458 --> 13:27.834
Colleen, uh,
we worked together.

13:27.834 --> 13:29.417
We made a book together.

13:29.417 --> 13:32.583
Now I want to make
a life together.

13:34.667 --> 13:36.125
Will you marry me?

13:36.125 --> 13:38.625
(slurping sounds)

13:43.083 --> 13:44.333
I liked the last one better,

13:44.333 --> 13:46.041
when you compared her
to a river.

13:46.041 --> 13:47.375
Powerful stuff.

13:47.375 --> 13:48.709
Whatcha doing?

13:48.709 --> 13:50.417
I'm sucking out these donut guts

13:50.417 --> 13:52.333
and putting them back in.

13:52.333 --> 13:55.083
And no one's the wiser.

13:55.083 --> 13:56.500
-Hey, Soph.
-Hm?

13:56.500 --> 13:58.208
What you just heard,

13:58.208 --> 14:00.291
I need you to keep
that quiet, okay?

14:00.291 --> 14:03.208
And I need you to put
these donut carcasses

14:03.208 --> 14:05.917
back on the buffet table.

14:05.917 --> 14:07.917
You got yourself a deal.

14:07.917 --> 14:11.542
♪♪

14:11.542 --> 14:13.083
Hi, Mom!

14:13.083 --> 14:14.792
Hi, Joanie, sweetheart.

14:14.792 --> 14:16.083
-Mwah!
-Mwah!

14:16.083 --> 14:17.458
I'm sorry I'm late,

14:17.458 --> 14:19.583
but my Uber
got caught in traffic.

14:19.583 --> 14:20.500
Oh.

14:20.500 --> 14:22.291
Hello, I'm Huber.

14:22.291 --> 14:24.125
He's my boyfriend.

14:24.125 --> 14:26.333
Oh, of course he is.

14:26.333 --> 14:28.542
I told him if he wants
to marry me,

14:28.542 --> 14:30.375
he's got to buy me a ring.

14:30.375 --> 14:33.667
Because my grandson
called dibs on mine.

14:33.667 --> 14:35.208
What?

14:35.208 --> 14:36.125
He did?

14:36.125 --> 14:37.750
I got to keep
my trap shut.

14:37.750 --> 14:39.792
Mom, get something to eat,

14:39.792 --> 14:41.083
and I'll be right back.

14:41.083 --> 14:42.542
I just have to find,

14:42.542 --> 14:43.959
um, somebody.

14:43.959 --> 14:45.583
♪♪

14:45.583 --> 14:46.542
All right.

14:46.542 --> 14:48.709
♪♪

14:48.709 --> 14:50.542
GiGi just told me
about the ring.

14:50.542 --> 14:51.458
Oh, no.

14:51.458 --> 14:53.500
JOAN: You don't have to
tell me what's going on,

14:53.500 --> 14:55.667
but if you're proposing
to Colleen,

14:55.667 --> 14:57.417
just blink.

15:03.166 --> 15:04.375
-Mom, I got to blink.
-Oh!

15:04.375 --> 15:06.417
-You're proposing--
-Shhh!

15:06.417 --> 15:08.709
Please, please, please
don't say anything, okay?

15:08.709 --> 15:10.583
I waited until this book signing
so I could do it on a night

15:10.583 --> 15:11.750
that's special to both of us.

15:11.750 --> 15:14.083
Oh, it will be special.

15:14.083 --> 15:16.125
And I know your dad
and I aren't married, honey,

15:16.125 --> 15:19.250
but that doesn't mean marriage
isn't a beautiful thing.

15:19.250 --> 15:22.500
And you two, you,
you just belong together.

15:24.125 --> 15:25.875
Thank you, Mom.

15:25.875 --> 15:27.834
All right, I got to go
get the ring from GiGi.

15:27.834 --> 15:30.417
Oh, she thinks her nurse
is her boyfriend,

15:30.417 --> 15:32.041
so just go along with it,
you know,

15:32.041 --> 15:33.709
so she doesn't make a scene
like she did

15:33.709 --> 15:35.792
when they canceled
<i>Walker, Texas Ranger.</i>

15:35.792 --> 15:37.125
Right.

15:37.125 --> 15:41.166
♪♪

15:41.166 --> 15:42.291
-Here you go.
-What, no.

15:42.291 --> 15:43.834
Have you forgotten
I can't drink?

15:43.834 --> 15:45.625
Oh, right, well,
I could drink for two.

15:45.625 --> 15:46.959
Yeah, okay,
just give it to me.

15:46.959 --> 15:47.875
I'm gonna pretend.

15:47.875 --> 15:49.417
I don't want
to tip off your sister.

15:49.417 --> 15:51.875
She's like a bomb-sniffing dog
for pregnant women.

15:51.875 --> 15:53.291
-Hey!
-Hi.

15:53.291 --> 15:55.250
-Getting your drink on?
-You know it.

15:55.250 --> 15:56.709
Oh, my God, I'm thirsty!

15:56.709 --> 15:59.208
(chuckling)

16:01.417 --> 16:03.000
MATT:
Oh, thank God.

16:03.000 --> 16:03.917
-Hi.
-Oh!

16:03.917 --> 16:05.166
There he is!

16:05.166 --> 16:07.250
My grandson,
the famous artist.

16:07.250 --> 16:08.166
Hi, GiGi.

16:08.166 --> 16:09.417
-Mwah!
-Mwah!

16:09.417 --> 16:11.917
I am so proud of you
and your book.

16:11.917 --> 16:14.000
Oh, thank you,
do you like it?

16:14.000 --> 16:15.625
No.

16:15.625 --> 16:19.208
I like stories that have
a message about manners

16:19.208 --> 16:21.625
and justice Texas-style.

16:21.625 --> 16:24.375
Okay, uh, GiGi, uh,
did you bring me anything?

16:24.375 --> 16:25.750
Oh, I almost forgot.

16:25.750 --> 16:28.166
(laughing)

16:28.166 --> 16:29.709
(exhaling)

16:29.709 --> 16:32.583
Don't let Huber
see you talking to me.

16:32.583 --> 16:35.000
He fills with jealousy and rage.

16:35.000 --> 16:35.917
Got it.

16:35.917 --> 16:37.750
♪♪

16:37.750 --> 16:38.959
All right, here we go.

16:38.959 --> 16:40.875
Get your camera ready.

16:40.875 --> 16:42.625
I am so excited.

16:42.625 --> 16:44.959
I thought this day
would never come.

16:44.959 --> 16:47.792
Me, neither.

16:47.792 --> 16:49.917
Okay, everyone, uh,
can we have your attention?

16:49.917 --> 16:51.667
Uh, thanks, son,
I'll take it from here.

16:51.667 --> 16:53.125
Dad, uh,
what are you doing?

16:53.125 --> 16:55.208
There's something I should've
done a long time ago.

16:55.208 --> 16:57.208
Joanie, would you come
up here for a moment?

16:57.208 --> 17:00.458
No, honey, I'm sure
whatever this is, it can wait.

17:00.458 --> 17:02.333
Oh, it's waited long enough.

17:02.333 --> 17:04.542
Uh, Joan Pirkle Short,

17:04.542 --> 17:07.166
you're not my wife
and you're not my ex-wife,

17:07.166 --> 17:09.375
but you're my soul mate.

17:09.375 --> 17:12.208
And I believe that--

17:12.208 --> 17:13.125
TIM: Hmm?

17:13.125 --> 17:16.417
JOHN: Keeping it fresh
keeps it special.

17:16.417 --> 17:19.166
-Okay.
-Joanie?

17:19.166 --> 17:22.125
Will you marry me again?

17:22.125 --> 17:23.917
Yes.

17:23.917 --> 17:25.333
Again.

17:25.333 --> 17:27.709
(applause)

17:27.709 --> 17:30.041
Are you kidding me?

17:30.041 --> 17:32.000
A toast, a toast to Mom and Dad!

17:32.000 --> 17:33.625
-Hear, hear!
-What's wrong with you?

17:33.625 --> 17:35.250
I'll tell you in a minute--
okay, everybody.

17:35.250 --> 17:36.458
Can, uh,
can we sit down, please?

17:36.458 --> 17:39.500
Wow, that was a surprise, huh?

17:39.500 --> 17:41.250
We weren't expecting that.

17:41.250 --> 17:42.333
But, uh, I tell you what,

17:42.333 --> 17:44.250
that's not the only big news

17:44.250 --> 17:45.875
that we have today.

17:45.875 --> 17:48.625
MATT: Um, uh...
HEATHER: Oh!

17:48.625 --> 17:49.792
Baby! Baby!

17:49.792 --> 17:50.917
Jen's pregnant!

17:50.917 --> 17:52.417
Son of a bitch.

17:53.792 --> 17:54.875
Surprise.

17:54.875 --> 17:56.792
(all cheering)

17:56.792 --> 17:58.667
Ooh, another grandbaby!

17:58.667 --> 18:00.166
GREG:
We wanted to wait to tell you

18:00.166 --> 18:01.750
until I got my job back, but...

18:01.750 --> 18:03.208
You lost your job?

18:03.208 --> 18:05.083
-Yeah.
-He's an inventor now.

18:05.083 --> 18:06.875
(chuckles)

18:06.875 --> 18:08.417
Okay, all right.

18:08.417 --> 18:10.667
Anybody else got any, uh,
big announcements to make?

18:10.667 --> 18:12.375
Bombshells to drop?
Surprises?

18:12.375 --> 18:14.333
No, everyone's good?

18:14.333 --> 18:15.542
Okay, oh, hey, Tyler.

18:15.542 --> 18:17.291
What about you?
You got anything?

18:19.667 --> 18:21.208
We got married.

18:21.208 --> 18:22.166
What?

18:22.166 --> 18:23.667
Is this a joke?

18:23.667 --> 18:26.959
No, this ring is no joke.

18:26.959 --> 18:28.083
Thanks, GiGi.

18:28.083 --> 18:29.583
Tyler got the ring?

18:29.583 --> 18:31.875
You are way too young
to be married!

18:31.875 --> 18:33.667
Why aren't you
saying anything?

18:33.667 --> 18:36.208
He can't hear you,
he just got laid.

18:36.208 --> 18:40.125
Dude, why isn't everyone
doing it all the time?

18:40.125 --> 18:41.500
GiGi?

18:41.500 --> 18:43.125
GIGI: Cuff links.

18:43.125 --> 18:45.417
To remember this night by.

18:45.417 --> 18:47.625
Don't sell them for grass.

18:47.625 --> 18:51.750
♪♪

18:51.750 --> 18:53.375
Okay.

18:53.375 --> 18:54.667
-You okay?
-Huh?

18:54.667 --> 18:55.792
Oh, yeah, to hell with it.

18:55.792 --> 18:57.208
Don't even want
to do it anymore.

18:57.208 --> 18:58.625
What, what are you
talking about?

18:58.625 --> 18:59.792
Do what, do what anymore?

18:59.792 --> 19:02.000
Ask you to marry me.

19:02.000 --> 19:03.583
You were gonna ask me
to marry you?

19:03.583 --> 19:05.250
Yeah, but who cares now?
It's stupid.

19:05.250 --> 19:07.458
I mean, I'm just gonna
look like a copycat.

19:07.458 --> 19:09.792
-Matt?
-What?

19:09.792 --> 19:14.417
♪♪

19:14.417 --> 19:16.458
-Come with me.
-Okay.

19:16.458 --> 19:21.625
♪♪

19:21.625 --> 19:24.291
Okay, this obviously didn't
go the way that I planned,

19:24.291 --> 19:26.375
but nothing about us has.

19:26.375 --> 19:28.417
♪♪

19:28.417 --> 19:30.875
I love you.

19:30.875 --> 19:34.083
And that is one thing
that has not changed.

19:34.083 --> 19:35.834
And it never will.

19:35.834 --> 19:39.166
♪♪

19:39.166 --> 19:40.250
(chuckles)

19:40.250 --> 19:41.875
Colleen Brandon Ortega?

19:41.875 --> 19:44.125
♪♪

19:44.125 --> 19:45.291
This floor is wet.

19:45.291 --> 19:46.542
-Oh.
-Um,

19:46.542 --> 19:48.000
will you do me the honor of--

19:48.000 --> 19:49.750
man, I really hope
this is water--

19:49.750 --> 19:51.709
of, uh, making me

19:51.709 --> 19:53.458
the happiest man on Earth

19:53.458 --> 19:55.000
for the rest of my life?

19:55.000 --> 19:57.041
♪♪

19:57.041 --> 19:58.792
A pair of chicken cuff links?

19:58.792 --> 20:00.625
It's us.

20:00.625 --> 20:01.959
Please marry me.

20:01.959 --> 20:04.250
Yes, yes!

20:04.250 --> 20:06.375
I love you.
I love your whole crazy family.

20:06.375 --> 20:07.667
I love all of it,
I love you.

20:07.667 --> 20:09.208
Yes!

20:09.208 --> 20:11.709
(vocalizing)

20:11.709 --> 20:17.625
♪♪

20:17.625 --> 20:19.583
If this is gonna go
past kissing,

20:19.583 --> 20:21.417
I'm just gonna
sneak out of here.

20:27.542 --> 20:29.458
Guys?

20:29.458 --> 20:30.959
We're engaged.

20:30.959 --> 20:32.000
Ah!

20:32.000 --> 20:33.500
JOHN: Can someone stop this?

20:33.500 --> 20:35.208
She's so old.

20:35.208 --> 20:36.250
COLLEEN: Wow.

20:36.250 --> 20:39.125
That was not the reaction
I expected.

20:39.125 --> 20:41.625
(moaning)

20:46.583 --> 20:48.500
TIM:
I guess that is her boyfriend.

20:48.500 --> 20:55.458
♪♪

20:56.500 --> 21:03.500
♪♪
